text: Hey everyone! I’m Randle. I’ve been working in content marketing since 2014, and am currently Head of Content & Marketing at Skillcrush, a tech education platform. I live in Brooklyn but am back home in Texas right now, where my husband and I own a pizza place. Glad to be here!

text:
Curious question <@U0212N91C9K>—does Skillcrush see any demand for soft-skill education from its memberbase? I figure y'all have the "hard skills" stuff down to a science and also imagine that's the primary focus.

I ask as someone who's starting to specialize in creating so-called soft-skills educational content, and am curious if someone in your position would see that as something you'd out- or in-source, if at all.

text: Hey <@U01AHL8AGBB> We do have content on soft skills. Although I guess it depends what you mean by that! Skillcrush has curriculum on freelancing, getting job-ready, interviewing, etc. We’re updating all that stuff in-house, but I definitely see a general interest in that kind of career support for beginners in tech.
